> "A geometric progression with a > 0 and r > 0 satisfies: each term (from the third onward) equals the sum of the two preceding terms.

>

> (a) Find the common ratio r.

> (b) Show that the logarithms of the terms form an arithmetic progression."



**Result:** Elegant bidirectional problem revealing φ through multidirectional solving.



